{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed63ee1c-2354-4c98-a6ee-840767f8e88f","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Basic API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --client-id <your-client-id>\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API (no controllers) with auth\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis --auth SingleOrg\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c3ba02c-af95-4a4e-ba4a-86b1b50044f7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/web development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the user is asking a general development question about web API project templates and authentication options. This isn't specifically about modifying code in the repository. Let me just answer from my knowledge about common web API templates and authentication options.\n\nCommon options include:\n- ASP.NET Core Web API (dotnet new webapi)\n- Express.js\n- FastAPI (Python)\n- etc.\n\nFor .NET specifically (given the repository context mentions dotnet plugins):\n\n\nThe basic Web API template can be scaffolded with `dotnet new webapi`, and for authentication I can choose between individual user accounts, Microsoft identity platform integration, Windows authentication, or no authentication depending on the requirements.","outputTokens":473,"requestId":"E82C:10C8FF:C09059:CD766B:6A0AFF74"},"id":"530f71c0-cca5-4000-bdc0-051878db3988","timestamp":"2026-05-18T12:01:09.365Z","parentId":"89976e95-4518-4e97-9713-b3514a5779b8"}
